Hands-On Tutorials for Covariate Adjustment in Randomized Trials

Binary Outcomes: Standardization (G-Computation)

Josh Betz (jbetz@jhu.edu), Kelly Van Lancker (kvanlan3@jhu.edu), and Michael Rosenblum (mrosen@jhu.edu)

2025-03-23

1 Fixed Sample Size

set.seed(12345) # Set seed for Reproducibility
alpha_design <- 0.05
power_design <- 0.80
test_sides <- 2
p0_design <- 0.25
p1_design <- 0.38
pr_missing <- 0.20

risk_difference_design <- p1_design - p0_design

risk_difference_design
## [1] 0.13

es_h_design <- pwr::ES.h(p1 = p1_design, p2 = p0_design)

es_h_design
## [1] 0.2812329

n_per_arm_fixed <-
  pwr::pwr.2p.test(
    h = es_h_design,
    sig.level = alpha_design,
    power = power_design
  )$n %>% ceiling()

n_per_arm_fixed
## [1] 199

2 Set Up Group Sequential Design

2.1 O-F: Efficacy Only Setup

type_of_design_asof <- "asOF"
type_beta_spending_asof <- "none"
information_rates <- c(0.50, 0.75, 1.00)

trial_design_asof <-
  rpact::getDesignGroupSequential(
    alpha = alpha_design,
    beta = 1 - power_design,
    sided = test_sides,
    informationRates = information_rates,
    typeOfDesign = type_of_design_asof,
    typeBetaSpending = type_beta_spending_asof
  )

trial_design_asof

Design parameters and output of group sequential design

User defined parameters

  • Type of design: OBrien & Fleming type alpha spending
  • Information rates: 0.500, 0.750, 1.000
  • Significance level: 0.0500
  • Type II error rate: 0.2000
  • Test: two-sided

Derived from user defined parameters

  • Maximum number of stages: 3

Default parameters

  • Stages: 1, 2, 3
  • Two-sided power: FALSE
  • Futility bounds (non-binding): -Inf, -Inf
  • Binding futility: FALSE
  • Tolerance: 1e-08
  • Type of beta spending: none

Output

  • Cumulative alpha spending: 0.003051, 0.019299, 0.050000
  • Critical values: 2.963, 2.359, 2.014
  • Stage levels (one-sided): 0.001525, 0.009162, 0.022000

2.2 O-F: Efficacy Only Bounds

trial_design_asof$criticalValues
## [1] 2.962588 2.359018 2.014084

plot(trial_design_asof)

2.3 O-F: Efficacy + Futility Setup

type_of_design_asof_bsof <- "asOF"
type_beta_spending_asof_bsof <- "bsOF"
information_rates <- c(0.50, 0.75, 1.00)

trial_design_asof_bsof <-
  rpact::getDesignGroupSequential(
    alpha = alpha_design,
    beta = 1 - power_design,
    sided = test_sides,
    informationRates = information_rates,
    typeOfDesign = type_of_design_asof_bsof,
    typeBetaSpending = type_beta_spending_asof_bsof
  )

trial_design_asof_bsof

Design parameters and output of group sequential design

User defined parameters

  • Type of design: OBrien & Fleming type alpha spending
  • Information rates: 0.500, 0.750, 1.000
  • Significance level: 0.0500
  • Type II error rate: 0.2000
  • Test: two-sided
  • Type of beta spending: OBrien & Fleming type beta spending

Derived from user defined parameters

  • Maximum number of stages: 3

Default parameters

  • Stages: 1, 2, 3
  • Two-sided power: FALSE
  • Binding futility: FALSE
  • Beta adjustment: TRUE
  • Tolerance: 1e-08

Output

  • Power: 0.1971, 0.5915, 0.8000
  • Futility bounds (non-binding): 0.655, 1.398
  • Cumulative alpha spending: 0.003051, 0.019299, 0.050000
  • Cumulative beta spending: 0.06993, 0.13892, 0.20000
  • Critical values: 2.963, 2.359, 2.014
  • Stage levels (one-sided): 0.001525, 0.009162, 0.022000

3 Set Up Group Sequential Analyses

For more details, see impart documentation

3.1 Set Information Targets

# Precision a.k.a. Information required for 
information_single_stage <-
  impart::required_information_single_stage(
    delta = risk_difference_design,
    alpha = alpha_design,
    power = power_design
  )

information_single_stage
## [1] 464.4308

# Inflate information level to account for multiple testing
information_adaptive_asof <-
  impart::required_information_sequential(
    information_single_stage = information_single_stage,
    trial_design = trial_design_asof
  )

information_adaptive_asof
## [1] 473.5487

information_adaptive_asof_bsof <-
  impart::required_information_sequential(
    information_single_stage = information_single_stage,
    trial_design = trial_design_asof_bsof
  )

information_adaptive_asof_bsof
## [1] 527.0975

3.2 Set Up Monitored Design

monitored_design_asof <-
  initialize_monitored_design(
    trial_design = trial_design_asof,
    null_value = 0,
    maximum_sample_size = 280,
    information_target = information_adaptive_asof,
    orthogonalize = TRUE,
    rng_seed_analysis = 54321
  )

monitored_design_asof_bsof <-
  initialize_monitored_design(
    trial_design = trial_design_asof_bsof,
    null_value = 0,
    maximum_sample_size = 280,
    information_target = information_adaptive_asof_bsof,
    orthogonalize = TRUE,
    rng_seed_analysis = 54321
  )

3.3 O-F Efficacy: Analysis 1

interim_analysis_asof_1 <-
  monitored_analysis(
    data = sim_miii_asof_ia_1,
    monitored_design = monitored_design_asof,
    estimation_function = standardization,
    estimation_arguments = 
      list(
        estimand = "difference",
        outcome_formula = 
          mrs_365d_binary ~ tx + age + male + hx_cvd + hx_hyperlipidemia +
          on_anticoagulants + on_antiplatelets + ich_location + ich_s_volume +
          ivh_s_volume + gcs_category,
        family = binomial,
        treatment_column = "tx",
        outcome_indicator_column = ".r_3"
      ),
    correction_function = standardization_correction
  )

# Decision
interim_analysis_asof_1$interim_analysis_1$decision_detail
## [1] "Continue - stage 1 of 3"
